sense.s:
The first of these phrases is said also to signify He removed, or took off, its 
								zujR 
								from the spear: (A:) IAar is related to have said thus; but he is also related to have said that this signification is not allowable. (TA.)

Q. 4. AizoHalafRa, as also AizolaHafRa, (Mgh, K,) He was, or became, far; he stood, or kept, aloof; (A 'Obeyd, Mgh, TA;) he removed, withdrew, or retired to a distance; (A 'Obeyd, Mgh, K, TA;) as also 
							tazaHolafa↓; (TA;) Eano kacaA 
								from such a thing: (Mgh:) for ex., from adultery, or fornication. (A 'Obeyd, Mgh, TA.)

Applied to a horse, (assumed tropical:) 
								Of middling make; 
								muqotadiru Alxaloqi or muqotadaru Alxlq: (so in different copies of the K:) thus expl. in the M. (TA.)

(tropical:) 
								Anything that is taken as a lord in the place of God; (S;) a thing, (K,) or anything, (AO, A,) that is worshipped in the place of God; 


							(AO, A, K;) as also zuwnN, with n: or a particular idol which was adorned with jewels, in the country of Ed-Dádar (AldRaAdar [a name I nowhere find]). (TA.)
